CONVERSATION TITLE: Opportunity at Frontier Dental Supply Inc. - Purchasing and Inventory Analyst
SUBJECT: Opportunity at Frontier Dental Supply Inc. - Purchasing and Inventory Analyst
CONTENT: Hi Marcio,   My name is Vanessa and I am the Talent Acquisition Partner at Frontier Dental Supply, Inc. We are a B2B retailer selling quality, top brand dental supplies to dentists and dental practices across North America.   We're on the lookout for a dynamic and experienced Purchasing and Inventory Analyst to join our expanding Purchasing Team. This role involves overseeing purchasing and inventory processes, collaborating with the Director, Purchasing to establish metrics and identify cost-saving opportunities.   The Analyst will manage a global purchasing organization, optimize procurement based on sales forecasts, and utilize data analytics tools like Power BI, Excel, and SQL to drive continuous improvement. This role will directly impacts our bottom line and contributes to our ongoing success.  ***Please note that this role is primarily onsite/hybrid at our Concord office (Keele & Steeles) on a regular basis.***  Click here for the full job posting:  https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/3860328388  Read our employees' reviews on our Glassdoor page: https://www.glassdoor.ca/Reviews/Frontier-Dental-Supply-Reviews-E1529514.htm   If you thrive in a fast-paced environment, excel at detailed coordination, and enjoy making a real impact on operational efficiency, I would love to connect with you!  Regards,  Vanessa To Human Resources Professional | Talent Acquisition | People & Culture

SUBJECT: Let's set up an interview!
CONTENT: Hey there Marcio,   Are you interested in using your background in ERP and the distribution industry to become a Microsoft Business Central Consultant?   For this role, you would be employed directly with a Microsoft Partner, earning salary and benefits from day 1, while we train you to earn your Microsoft Consultant certifications.  This is a hybrid role (2x a month in office for pre-planned team building- location is 926 Nashville RD Kleinburg ON- must live within 90 minutes of office) with up to 10% travel in the Toronto area to client sites.    Requirements include: -4+ years of experience in Canada -ERP implementation experience  -Accounting and Distribution modules in the ERP -Distribution, Supply Chain or Manufacturing industry experience  -Drivers License and access to a vehicle   If you have those requirements, please use this link to schedule a 15 minute phone call: https://calendly.com/l-gilardi/15min  Talk soon!  Lydia Gilardi Internal Recruitment Manager

Strong communication and writing skills; 7. Ability to learn fast; 8. Ability to accurately perform repetitive and routine duties and tasks.

CONVERSATION TITLE: MS in Law at Northwestern: Exclusively for STEM Backgrounds
CONTENT:
Dear Marcio,


Based on your background, we believe you would be a great fit for our Master of Science in Law (MSL) program at Northwestern Pritzker School of Law. By focusing on the intersection of Law, Business, and Technology, the MSL helps students prepare for the changing and expanding role of the modern STEM professional. MSL graduates become more well-rounded and can think beyond the technical and step into cross-functional and leadership roles. The MSL teaches students to communicate across disciplines; bring ideas to market; develop, protect, and manage intellectual property; and navigate the legal and regulatory structures that exist in STEM settings.


The curriculum is innovative and completely distinctive, providing practical, focused, business-centered legal training in the following three main areas:


  • Business Law & Entrepreneurship
  • Intellectual Property & Patent Design
  • Regulatory Analysis & Strategy

The MSL also focuses on skills development in the areas of writing, oral communication, presentations, negotiations, and financial skills.


The MSL degree is offered in three formats: residential full-time, residential part-time, and online part-time. For more information, please download the MSL program brochure.


For a more extensive introduction to the MSL, please register for our Spring Open House, held remotely on Saturday, March 5, from 9:00 AM to 12:30 PM CST. Register to attend.


Open House attendees will: 

  • Learn more about the available formats, including online, residential, full-time, and part-time
  • Explore the MSL‚Äôs unique curriculum
  • Meet with MSL staff, students and faculty
  • Preview a class: RegTech: Transforming the Interaction of Regulators, Regulated Enterprises and Markets
  • Participate in a Q&A session with program staff and current students

Another great way to learn about the MSL program is through our one of our information sessions. Our next information session will be on Wednesday, March 16, at 5:30 PM CST. We will provide a comprehensive overview of the MSL program, including information on courses, scheduling, career paths, and more. We will also take questions from participants. Click here to register for the information session. 


We hope to see you at our upcoming events!


Sincerely,

Clinical Associate Professor of Law

Director, Master of Science in Law Program

Dear Marcio,


We trust you are fine.


We are reaching out to you as you are an active member of the air cargo community.


We would like to inform you that IATA has just released the new editions of the Dangerous Goods Regulations (DGR) and Cargo Standards Manuals, such as the Live Animals Regulations, the Temperature Control Regulations and the ULD Regulations, among others.


All these IATA regulations will be effective 1 January 2020 and are the industry reference to handle, store and fly air cargo shipments, covering all the information you need, from generic rules and regulations to specific cargo operations cases.


Many important updates have been introduced in these manuals (see a quick overview here) providing you, right now, with the necessary guidance to run, in 2020, a safe, secure and efficient air freight logistic.


Please visit our website to explore the full range of Cargo Standards Manuals, and select the ones relevant to your business: https://go.updates.iata.org/iatapublications2020


Do not hesitate to contact us if you need more information.

Best regards,


 

IATA
